What? No.

255
00:10:58.867 --> 00:11:01.328
-That's not a real movie.
-Oh. I promise you. it is.

256
00:11:01.411 --> 00:11:03.914
-Sam. you need to stop.
-Come on. he deserves

257
00:11:03.997 --> 00:11:07.334
to know that his girlfriend is going
to become the next Stephen King.

258
00:11:07.417 --> 00:11:10.587
that she's read
the entire Dark Tower series twice.

259
00:11:10.670 --> 00:11:15.467
she once wrote this 10.000-word blog post
about how Guillermo del Toro is overrated.

260
00:11:15.550 --> 00:11:19.638
she has this figurine of Jeff Goldblum
on her dresser from The Fly. and.

261
00:11:19.721 --> 00:11:23.100
well. of course you know
her favorite book.

262
00:11:26.353 --> 00:11:28.146
Wait. you do know. right?

263
00:11:29.981 --> 00:11:32.442
You haven't told him...?

264
00:11:32.526 --> 00:11:33.944
Frankenstein.

265
00:11:35.445 --> 00:11:39.157
Because Mary Shelley was 19
when she wrote it and a genius.

266
00:11:40.242 --> 00:11:41.785
A girl wrote that?

267
00:11:43.995 --> 00:11:46.748
Sam. can I talk to you. please?

268
00:11:50.794 --> 00:11:52.397
-What the fuck is wrong with you?
-I'm sorry. I...

269
00:11:52.421 --> 00:11:54.172
Why are you being such an asshole?

270
00:11:54.256 --> 00:11:55.924
I just wasn't expecting that. okay?

271
00:11:56.007 --> 00:11:57.926
You show up with a boyfriend?

272
00:11:58.009 --> 00:11:59.636
Oh. really?

273
00:11:59.719 --> 00:12:02.115
Maybe that's something you should have
thought about before you broke up with me.

274
00:12:02.139 --> 00:12:03.807
-I can date who I want. Sam.
-I know that.

275
00:12:03.890 --> 00:12:04.975
You made that very clear.

276
00:12:05.058 --> 00:12:06.369
-I know.
-Then what are you talking about?

277
00:12:06.393 --> 00:12:08.728
You just... you didn't have
to bring him here. did you.

278
00:12:08.812 --> 00:12:10.981
to Barry's Bay. to my family's restaurant?

279
00:12:11.064 --> 00:12:12.983
You wanted to rub this in my face.

280
00:12:13.066 --> 00:12:14.734
Oh. so what?

281
00:12:14.818 --> 00:12:17.612
It was a shitty thing you did.
breaking up with me for no reason.

282
00:12:17.696 --> 00:12:19.114
Percy. it wasn't for no reason.

283
00:12:19.197 --> 00:12:21.366
Yes. I get it. school's important.

284
00:12:21.450 --> 00:12:24.744
but you made the decision all by yourself
that I was going to stand in the way.

285
00:12:24.828 --> 00:12:26.389
-You didn't even give me a chance.
-I thought

286
00:12:26.413 --> 00:12:29.291
it would be too hard trying
to stay together long-distance.

287
00:12:29.374 --> 00:12:31.543
You should have trusted me.

288
00:12:31.626 --> 00:12:33.837
You should have trusted us.

289
00:12:36.173 --> 00:12:38.383
And I see that now.

290
00:12:40.844 --> 00:12:43.388
-Percy...
-Oh. no. no. no.

291
00:12:43.472 --> 00:12:45.307
No. you do not get to do that.

292
00:12:45.390 --> 00:12:47.684
You don't get to dump me and then feel bad

293
00:12:47.767 --> 00:12:49.978
and want me back
when you see me with someone else.

294
00:12:50.061 --> 00:12:51.605
So that's it?

295
00:12:51.688 --> 00:12:53.190
You made your choice. Sam.

296
00:12:54.274 --> 00:12:56.610
I need to go and find my boyfriend.

297
00:13:03.825 --> 00:13:07.037
♪ And it knows I'm imagining things ♪

298
00:13:07.120 --> 00:13:11.416
♪ I wonder if it's time to explore it ♪

299
00:13:11.500 --> 00:13:14.628
♪ Turn these thoughts
into matter with me ♪

300
00:13:26.723 --> 00:13:28.183
Delilah.

301
00:13:29.976 --> 00:13:31.311
I didn't know you were here.

302
00:13:31.394 --> 00:13:32.646
-Yeah.
-You're alone?

303
00:13:32.729 --> 00:13:35.232
-Eight. seven. six...
-Apparently. What-what about you?

304
00:13:35.315 --> 00:13:37.400
-Yeah. uh. flying solo these days.
-five. four.

305
00:13:37.484 --> 00:13:40.278
three. two. one!

306
00:13:40.362 --> 00:13:42.781
Happy New Year!

307
00:13:49.871 --> 00:13:52.332
-You wanna?
-Sure.

308
00:13:58.213 --> 00:14:01.550
♪ Your laughter. your loving touch ♪

309
00:14:05.595 --> 00:14:06.805
♪ Such a gift to me...

310
00:14:06.888 --> 00:14:08.181
There you are.

311
00:14:08.265 --> 00:14:10.183
Are you okay?

312
00:14:13.353 --> 00:14:17.274
♪ A special place in my heart ♪♪

313
00:14:19.734 --> 00:14:21.653
Where are you with The Tavern?

314
00:14:22.237 --> 00:14:24.197
-Is it wrong to keep it?
-No.

315
00:14:24.281 --> 00:14:25.782
Sue wanted you to have it.

316
00:14:25.865 --> 00:14:28.326
I just worry it'll make things weirder
with me and Sam.

317
00:14:28.410 --> 00:14:29.411
Okay. well.

318
00:14:29.494 --> 00:14:33.081
Sam is leaving in a few days. and you
and him cannot be in a relationship

319
00:14:33.164 --> 00:14:36.418
for a lot of reasons.

320
00:14:36.501 --> 00:14:39.546
So my legal opinion...

321
00:14:39.629 --> 00:14:41.047
What the fuck does it matter?

322
00:14:41.131 --> 00:14:42.549
It's about more than just Sam.

323
00:14:42.632 --> 00:14:46.344
It's about... it's about the person
that I want to be...

324
00:14:46.428 --> 00:14:49.014
-Mm.
-or think I could be.

325
00:14:51.474 --> 00:14:54.519
I-I think Barry's Bay could be
good for me.

326
00:14:54.603 --> 00:14:57.022
-Yeah.
-But also...

327
00:14:57.105 --> 00:14:59.232
But also? Oh. I don't like that.

328
00:14:59.316 --> 00:15:00.358
-Oh. nothing.
-No.

329
00:15:00.442 --> 00:15:01.901
-Percy.
-Mm-mm.

330
00:15:01.985 --> 00:15:04.946
What? You want me to say
some small childish part of me thought

331
00:15:05.030 --> 00:15:08.092
that when I came back. he'd tell me he'd
always loved me and we'd end up together?

332
00:15:08.116 --> 00:15:10.160
Yes. small part of me did.

333
00:15:10.243 --> 00:15:11.244
Mm-hmm.

334
00:15:11.328 --> 00:15:13.413
Only you know
he's with Beautiful Doctor Lady.

335
00:15:13.496 --> 00:15:16.124
Yes. I know. and if he found out

336
00:15:16.207 --> 00:15:18.084
-what I did...
-Ten years ago.

337
00:15:18.168 --> 00:15:19.586
He'd hate me forever.

338
00:15:19.669 --> 00:15:21.463
So it doesn't matter.

339
00:15:21.546 --> 00:15:23.548
Make the decision for you.

340
00:15:29.137 --> 00:15:30.972
Hi.

341
00:15:31.056 --> 00:15:32.891
-Hey.
-Hey. Jordie.

342
00:15:32.974 --> 00:15:34.100
You guys good?

343
00:15:34.184 --> 00:15:35.185
-Yeah.
-Mm-hmm.

344
00:15:35.268 --> 00:15:36.686
You okay?

345
00:15:37.270 --> 00:15:38.480
Yeah. totally.

346
00:15:39.064 --> 00:15:40.565
-Lying.
-Uh. Chantal.

347
00:15:40.649 --> 00:15:43.336
No. I-I've sat through thousands of hours
of depositions and interviews.

348
00:15:43.360 --> 00:15:46.196
He's lying very badly.

349
00:15:46.279 --> 00:15:47.280
Sorry.

350
00:15:47.364 --> 00:15:50.301
Yeah. it's fine. uh. just something
I don't think I'm supposed to talk about.

351
00:15:50.325 --> 00:15:52.035
-Then you shouldn't.
-Yeah. uh. absolutely.

352
00:15:52.118 --> 00:15:54.013
especially if it has to do
with Percy and The Tavern.

353
00:15:54.037 --> 00:15:55.437
Yeah. no. it doesn't. like. at all.

354
00:15:55.997 --> 00:15:57.165
Sam and Percy?

355
00:15:57.248 --> 00:16:00.502
No. it's Sam and not Percy.
so maybe just leave it there.

356
00:16:00.585 --> 00:16:02.545
So. Sam and someone else?

357
00:16:02.629 --> 00:16:04.047
Charlie? His mom?

358
00:16:04.130 --> 00:16:05.882
-Seriously. Chantal.
-Sam and Taylor?

359
00:16:06.800 --> 00:16:09.010
Sam and Taylor are breaking up.

360
00:16:09.094 --> 00:16:11.012
No. uh. like the opposite.

361
00:16:11.096 --> 00:16:12.806
The opposite?
What is the opposite?

362
00:16:14.557 --> 00:16:16.309
Oh. he's proposing?

363
00:16:16.393 --> 00:16:17.560
-What?
-Oh. fucking A.

364
00:16:17.644 --> 00:16:18.895
Is this what you do?

365
00:16:18.978 --> 00:16:20.563
Yeah. but you're also just very easy.

366
00:16:20.647 --> 00:16:22.065
Wait. wait. when is he proposing?

367
00:16:23.274 --> 00:16:24.859
Is-is Taylor coming back?

368
00:16:26.528 --> 00:16:27.570
Today?

369
00:16:27.654 --> 00:16:29.531
-He's proposing today?
-Yeah.

370
00:16:29.614 --> 00:16:31.534
You don't seem like you feel
too good about that.

371
00:16:31.574 --> 00:16:32.575
It's interesting.

372
00:16:32.659 --> 00:16:35.537
Well. how I feel about it
is that. uh. Sam thinks it's right

373
00:16:35.620 --> 00:16:37.831
and I. as his friend. support him.

374
00:16:37.914 --> 00:16:38.998
Lying again.

375
00:16:39.082 --> 00:16:42.377
Please... don't tell anyone.

376
00:16:44.087 --> 00:16:46.256
-You're terrifying.
-Thank you.

377
00:16:50.552 --> 00:16:52.595
-You okay?
-Yeah. yeah. of course. yeah.

378
00:16:52.679 --> 00:16:55.282
I mean. I knew he had a ring. and it's not
like. it's not like we can be together.

379
00:16:55.306 --> 00:16:56.599
Right? So...

380
00:16:57.767 --> 00:16:59.102
I need to sit down.

381
00:17:00.437 --> 00:17:05.608
Um. I-I barely know Sam.
and his girlfriend not at all.

382
00:17:05.692 --> 00:17:08.236
but proposing the same week
of your mom's funeral.

383
00:17:08.319 --> 00:17:11.656
the same week that his.
his childhood soulmate reappears. it's...

384
00:17:11.740 --> 00:17:13.050
there's panic written all over it.

385
00:17:13.074 --> 00:17:17.954
No. I can't go down some rabbit hole of-of
thinking that Sam's making a mistake.

386
00:17:18.037 --> 00:17:20.874
or worse. that he-he's doing this
because of me.

387
00:17:20.957 --> 00:17:22.935
Okay. but can we at least admit
that the timing is suspicious?

388
00:17:22.959 --> 00:17:25.753
No. Sam and I. we don't have.
we don't have a future.

389
00:17:25.837 --> 00:17:27.338
Not now. not ever.

390
00:17:27.422 --> 00:17:29.108
-Percy...
-No. no. I'm. really. I'm fine. I'm fine.

391
00:17:29.132 --> 00:17:30.508
I just. I need to take a walk.

392
00:17:30.592 --> 00:17:32.469
Um. I'll meet you back at the motel. okay?

393
00:17:32.552 --> 00:17:33.636
Okay.

394
00:17:34.971 --> 00:17:36.407
Have you seen Sam yet?

395
00:17:36.431 --> 00:17:38.266
No. I told you. I just got here.

396
00:17:38.349 --> 00:17:39.702
Wait. so he wasn't there to greet you

397
00:17:39.726 --> 00:17:40.935
when you arrived?

398
00:17:41.019 --> 00:17:43.062
No. I mean. he wouldn't have known
I was coming.

399
00:17:43.146 --> 00:17:44.773
We haven't spoken since New Year's.

400
00:17:44.856 --> 00:17:46.083
I thought you two were so connected.

401
00:17:46.107 --> 00:17:48.985
he would have sensed
that you dumped Mason.

402
00:17:49.068 --> 00:17:50.737
which was a big mistake. by the way.

403
00:17:50.820 --> 00:17:52.197
That boy is so into you.

404
00:17:52.280 --> 00:17:53.865
I just...

405
00:17:53.948 --> 00:17:54.949
He's...

406
00:17:55.033 --> 00:17:56.534
Not Sam?

407
00:17:56.618 --> 00:17:57.619
Exactly.

408
00:17:57.702 --> 00:18:00.330
Percy. he does not deserve you. okay?

409
00:18:00.413 --> 00:18:02.373
You are so much better than that.
I just...

410
00:18:02.457 --> 00:18:03.750
Whatever.

411
00:18:03.833 --> 00:18:05.352
I'm gonna be there in a week
so that you're not alone.

412
00:18:05.376 --> 00:18:06.920
-Oh. God.
-What. what?

413
00:18:07.003 --> 00:18:08.046
-God. God.
-What?

414
00:18:08.129 --> 00:18:09.130
I think I saw him.

415
00:18:09.214 --> 00:18:11.090
-Huh?
-I think I saw Sam. but I-I'm not sure.

416
00:18:11.174 --> 00:18:12.693
-I think it was him.
-So. are you. like. hiding from him?

417
00:18:12.717 --> 00:18:14.260
Do you have a zit?

418
00:18:15.220 --> 00:18:16.387
Percy.

419
00:18:16.471 --> 00:18:17.889
Hi. sorry.

420
00:18:17.972 --> 00:18:19.390
I-I thought that was you.

421
00:18:19.474 --> 00:18:20.767
When did you get here?

422
00:18:20.850 --> 00:18:22.435
I got to go.

423
00:18:22.519 --> 00:18:24.521
-Oh. just today.
-What?

424
00:18:24.604 --> 00:18:25.605
I wish I would've known.

425
00:18:25.688 --> 00:18:27.088
I would've been there to greet you.

426
00:18:27.440 --> 00:18:29.192
So. how have you been?

427
00:18:29.275 --> 00:18:32.779
Good. good. yeah. yeah. just-just busy.

428
00:18:32.862 --> 00:18:35.448
you know. with school
and The Tavern and...

429
00:18:36.533 --> 00:18:38.368
Look. I wanted to apologize
for New Year's.

430
00:18:38.451 --> 00:18:40.078
-Oh. you don't have to.
-No. I do.

431
00:18:40.161 --> 00:18:44.123
I was a complete jerk. and you're right.
you can date whoever you want.

432
00:18:44.207 --> 00:18:46.084
I was just jealous.

433
00:18:47.919 --> 00:18:49.045
Really. jealous?

434
00:18:49.128 --> 00:18:52.382
Yeah. yeah. and it was completely unfair
to you. and I'm.

435
00:18:52.465 --> 00:18:54.217
I'm really. really sorry.

436
00:18:55.218 --> 00:18:57.428
It's okay. Sam.

437
00:18:57.512 --> 00:18:58.763
Thank you.

438
00:18:59.848 --> 00:19:02.517
Also. I just missed
talking to you.

439
00:19:02.600 --> 00:19:03.977
Me. too.

440
00:19:04.060 --> 00:19:06.145
I really hope we can hang out this summer.

441
00:19:08.273 --> 00:19:09.399
I-I mean. the four of us.

442
00:19:10.984 --> 00:19:12.151
The four of us?

443
00:19:12.235 --> 00:19:15.238
Yeah. yeah. you know. you and Mason.
if he comes back to visit.

444
00:19:15.321 --> 00:19:16.906
and me and my girlfriend.

445
00:19:17.991 --> 00:19:21.786
Oh. yeah. sure. okay. fun.

446
00:19:21.870 --> 00:19:23.413
Yeah.

447
00:19:23.496 --> 00:19:24.765
All right. well. I have
to get to The Tavern.

448
00:19:24.789 --> 00:19:28.001
My shift's about to start. but...
I'm glad you're back.

449
00:19:28.918 --> 00:19:29.919
Yeah.

450
00:19:38.553 --> 00:19:39.554
What happened?

451
00:19:39.637 --> 00:19:41.490
Tell Mason I need
to get back together with him.

452
00:19:41.514 --> 00:19:43.892
and bring him with you
when you come. okay?

453
00:19:47.520 --> 00:19:48.521
Hi. Percy.

454
00:19:48.605 --> 00:19:50.982
Drew. what are you doing here?

455
00:19:51.065 --> 00:19:54.903
Oh. him and Jake and some of their buddies
decided to go on a little fishing trip.

456
00:19:54.986 --> 00:19:56.738
and then he thought he would surprise me.

457
00:19:56.821 --> 00:19:57.822
Isn't that fun?

458
00:19:57.906 --> 00:19:59.741
I figured she might need new clothes.

459
00:20:00.325 --> 00:20:02.035
Which I appreciate.

460
00:20:02.118 --> 00:20:04.871
but. um. that's not all he brought.

461
00:20:06.414 --> 00:20:07.957
He's sick?

462
00:20:08.041 --> 00:20:10.185
Why am I worried about having children
when I already have one?

463
00:20:10.209 --> 00:20:11.920
-He means well.
-Of course he means well.

464
00:20:12.003 --> 00:20:14.172
He is a kind and sweet person.

465
00:20:14.255 --> 00:20:19.385
It is why I love him. but he is a child.
and I don't want to be his mommy.

466
00:20:22.597 --> 00:20:26.100
It's fine. I feel...
I'm-I'm better. it's fine.

467
00:20:27.143 --> 00:20:28.811
How are you with the Sam of it all?

468
00:20:28.895 --> 00:20:30.271
Oh. I'm fine.

469
00:20:30.355 --> 00:20:31.981
Mm-hmm.

470
00:20:32.065 --> 00:20:33.066
Don't lie to me.

471
00:20:33.149 --> 00:20:34.567
I'm not lying.

472
00:20:34.651 --> 00:20:36.110
Mm-hmm?

473
00:20:36.194 --> 00:20:38.404
Okay. I'm not fine. but I will be.

474
00:20:38.488 --> 00:20:39.864
I just need a distraction.

475
00:20:42.200 --> 00:20:44.869
Chantal. hey. I thought
this was the right room.

476
00:20:44.953 --> 00:20:47.747
Percy. hi.

477
00:20:48.831 --> 00:20:50.041
Dude. are you taking a nap?

478
00:20:50.124 --> 00:20:52.728
Yeah. he's sick. he's gonna be
in here for a while. so you should go on.

479
00:20:52.752 --> 00:20:55.213
Or I could hang out.
see if he feels better.

480
00:20:55.296 --> 00:20:56.214
Doubtful.

481
00:20:56.297 --> 00:20:57.715
You know what?

482
00:20:57.799 --> 00:20:59.842
I'm gonna show you around the town.

483
00:20:59.926 --> 00:21:01.052
I know all the secret spots.

484
00:21:01.135 --> 00:21:02.553
It's gonna be really fun.

485
00:21:02.637 --> 00:21:03.846
-Cool.
-Ex-Excuse me.

486
00:21:03.930 --> 00:21:05.223
-Sorry.
-What?

487
00:21:06.724 --> 00:21:08.726
No. you cannot just fuck
your bad feelings away.

488
00:21:08.810 --> 00:21:10.520
Chantal. honey. watch me.

489
00:21:12.647 --> 00:21:14.190
-Shall we?
-We shall.

490
00:21:14.273 --> 00:21:16.693
♪ My friends are the stars...

491
00:21:16.776 --> 00:21:19.570
-How do I look?
-For the tenth time. you look amazing.

492
00:21:19.654 --> 00:21:20.989
Relax.

493
00:21:22.115 --> 00:21:23.282
Hi. Welcome to The Tavern.

494
00:21:23.366 --> 00:21:24.450
-For three?
-Yeah.

495
00:21:24.534 --> 00:21:26.174
Is Sam working? Can we be in his section?

496
00:21:26.244 --> 00:21:27.245
We're friends.

497
00:21:27.328 --> 00:21:29.163
S-Sure. Yeah.

498
00:21:31.207 --> 00:21:33.042
I'm really glad you were able to come.

499
00:21:33.126 --> 00:21:35.420
Should I pretend I wasn't basically
staring at my phone.

500
00:21:35.503 --> 00:21:37.005
waiting for you to call?

501
00:21:39.382 --> 00:21:40.717
You are very charming.

502
00:21:40.800 --> 00:21:41.926
I know.

503
00:21:42.927 --> 00:21:44.095
But it's true.

504
00:21:46.681 --> 00:21:48.391
Oh. Thank you.

505
00:21:48.474 --> 00:21:50.685
Wait. so are we gonna see that guy

506
00:21:50.768 --> 00:21:52.478
who kept talking about
your love of horror?

507
00:21:52.562 --> 00:21:53.771
What?

508
00:21:53.855 --> 00:21:55.523
Doesn't his family own this restaurant?

509
00:21:55.606 --> 00:21:59.027
Oh. yeah. Unfortunately.
there's. like. nowhere else to eat.

510
00:21:59.110 --> 00:22:00.278
-And his name is...
-Sam.

511
00:22:03.656 --> 00:22:06.075
Hey. Delilah. good to see you.

512
00:22:06.159 --> 00:22:08.077
-Mason. welcome back.
-What's up. man?

513
00:22:08.161 --> 00:22:10.038
Wait. are you our waiter?

514
00:22:10.121 --> 00:22:11.873
-Yeah.
-We'll come here every day.

515
00:22:11.956 --> 00:22:13.207
Me. Percy and Mason.

516
00:22:13.291 --> 00:22:14.959
Mm. Cool.

517
00:22:15.043 --> 00:22:16.502
How long you guys in town?

518
00:22:16.586 --> 00:22:21.799
Uh. Delilah's here for a month.
and Mason can only stay a few days.

519
00:22:21.883 --> 00:22:25.845
He's been invited to this super
competitive hockey camp in Chicago.

520
00:22:25.928 --> 00:22:27.930
-It's not that big of a deal.
-Uh. it is.

521
00:22:28.014 --> 00:22:29.640
It's the top 50 players in the country.

522
00:22:29.724 --> 00:22:31.035
-Mm-hmm.
-He's being modest.

523
00:22:31.059 --> 00:22:32.894
Well. sounds way better than working here.

524
00:22:32.977 --> 00:22:35.271
carrying out the thousandth order
of burgers and fries.

525
00:22:35.354 --> 00:22:38.608
Your summer can't be all that bad.
I hear you have a new girlfriend.

526
00:22:38.691 --> 00:22:40.693
Uh. yeah. Yeah. Lake.

527
00:22:40.777 --> 00:22:43.196
Your girlfriend's name is Lake.
and you live on a lake?

528
00:22:43.279 --> 00:22:45.073
Yeah. she's heard all the jokes.

529
00:22:45.156 --> 00:22:47.533
Anyway. you guys met her.
She's the hostess.

530
00:22:50.661 --> 00:22:52.497
Oh.

531
00:22:52.580 --> 00:22:54.165
Oh.

532
00:22:54.248 --> 00:22:56.125
So...

533
00:22:56.209 --> 00:22:57.585
so you guys work together?

534
00:22:57.668 --> 00:22:59.837
You see each other every day?

535
00:22:59.921 --> 00:23:01.005
Yeah. pretty much.

536
00:23:03.841 --> 00:23:06.552
Okay. well. I'm gonna get you guys
some waters while you decide.

537
00:23:06.636 --> 00:23:08.346
Here. take your time.

538
00:23:10.807 --> 00:23:12.558
He's much cooler than at New Year's.

539
00:23:12.642 --> 00:23:14.477
He was kind of a prick.

540
00:23:17.563 --> 00:23:19.065
I'll be right back. Bathroom.

541
00:23:30.618 --> 00:23:32.954
Percy. Hey. You're back.

542
00:23:33.037 --> 00:23:35.081
-Hey. Jordie.
-You. uh. you alone?

543
00:23:35.164 --> 00:23:36.582
Yeah.

544
00:23:37.625 --> 00:23:39.585
I mean. no. Uh. Delilah's here.

545
00:23:39.669 --> 00:23:43.297
Cool. cool. Uh. so...
is she seeing anyone?

546
00:23:43.381 --> 00:23:45.174
-No. Not right now.
-Oh.

547
00:23:47.468 --> 00:23:48.636
You met Lake?

548
00:23:49.262 --> 00:23:51.931
Yeah. How long have
she and Sam been dating?

549
00:23:52.014 --> 00:23:55.434
Wouldn't call it "dating."
I mean. she's been after him all year.

550
00:23:55.518 --> 00:23:59.105
and once she started working here. I mean.
our boy's only flesh and blood.

551
00:23:59.188 --> 00:24:02.525
Oh. So-so. it isn't serious?

552
00:24:02.608 --> 00:24:04.694
-Not that I. you know. care.
-No. no. no. no.

553
00:24:04.777 --> 00:24:06.296
Can you imagine saying.
"I love you. Lake"?

554
00:24:06.320 --> 00:24:07.738
Be like saying.

555
00:24:07.822 --> 00:24:09.282
"I love you. Cloud."

556
00:24:09.365 --> 00:24:12.577
Or. "I love you. Tree."
I don't know.

557
00:24:13.786 --> 00:24:15.705
I love you.

558
00:24:15.788 --> 00:24:18.166
I should've said that
the moment I saw you.

559
00:24:20.168 --> 00:24:22.503
And I missed you so much.

560
00:24:22.587 --> 00:24:25.965
I love you. too. And I missed you.

561
00:24:26.048 --> 00:24:28.676
Gosh. it feels like you've been gone
longer than two days.

562
00:24:28.759 --> 00:24:31.804
A lot's happened.

563
00:24:31.888 --> 00:24:36.726
Yeah. I mean. all that stuff with Percy
and The Tavern. I mean. are you...

564
00:24:36.809 --> 00:24:38.186
are you doing okay?

565
00:24:38.269 --> 00:24:41.606
Yeah. well. we're contesting the will.
so we'll see.

566
00:24:41.689 --> 00:24:44.400
Why do you think your mom did it?

567
00:24:44.483 --> 00:24:46.652
I wish I knew.

568
00:24:46.736 --> 00:24:49.989
Sam. I'm really trying not to be
a jealous girlfriend here. but

569
00:24:50.072 --> 00:24:52.509
do you think your mom wanted you and Percy
to get back together?

570
00:24:52.533 --> 00:24:54.535
No. absolutely not.

571
00:24:54.619 --> 00:24:56.662
Look. she made her will in 2021.

572
00:24:56.746 --> 00:24:59.466
If she wanted me back with Percy.
she had five years to tell me that.

573
00:24:59.540 --> 00:25:00.660
I mean. how can you be sure?

574
00:25:00.708 --> 00:25:02.960
I mean. she told Charlie
to invite her to the funeral.

575
00:25:03.044 --> 00:25:07.840
Okay. Look. my mom cared about her.
but that doesn't matter.

576
00:25:08.507 --> 00:25:12.762
Because whatever happens
with Percy and The Tavern.

577
00:25:12.845 --> 00:25:14.347
that's the past.

578
00:25:16.057 --> 00:25:17.600
You're my future.

579
00:25:19.352 --> 00:25:20.686
I like the sound of that.

580
00:25:31.155 --> 00:25:34.200
I have got something very special
planned for tonight.

581
00:25:34.283 --> 00:25:36.327
Oh. Okay.

582
00:25:37.453 --> 00:25:40.206
-I'm gonna take your stuff upstairs.
-Sounds good.

583
00:25:44.835 --> 00:25:46.170
Fuck!

584
00:25:46.254 --> 00:25:48.130
Fucking fuck!

585
00:25:49.215 --> 00:25:51.968
I take it the meeting
with the lawyer did not go well.

586
00:25:52.051 --> 00:25:55.763
"Sue Florek was of sound mind"

587
00:25:55.846 --> 00:25:58.849
and body when she drafted the will.

588
00:25:59.475 --> 00:26:03.729
"The chances of you
successfully contesting are zero."

589
00:26:05.398 --> 00:26:07.483
No. it did not go well.

590
00:26:09.986 --> 00:26:13.322
Well... I guess that's that.

591
00:26:14.115 --> 00:26:15.449
Hold on.

592
00:26:15.533 --> 00:26:18.244
Charlie. it's clear
Percy's getting The Tavern.

593
00:26:18.327 --> 00:26:20.472
I'll just deal with her now. That's all.
It's just business.

594
00:26:20.496 --> 00:26:24.542
-Delilah. I'm not done fighting.
-Why do you care if she gets it?

595
00:26:24.625 --> 00:26:26.210
Didn't you want to sell it?

596
00:26:26.294 --> 00:26:29.255
Because this belongs to me and Sam.
We deserve the money. not her.

597
00:26:30.339 --> 00:26:35.636
Look. I understand that your mom's choice
is very confusing.

598
00:26:35.720 --> 00:26:37.847
-Um...
-I don't even care about the money.

599
00:26:37.930 --> 00:26:41.183
I just... Why didn't she want us
to have it? I don't...

600
00:26:41.267 --> 00:26:43.102
I...

601
00:26:43.185 --> 00:26:46.230
Look. tell Whit I will think of something.

602
00:26:47.356 --> 00:26:50.234
Well. Whit is no longer a factor
in The Tavern.

603
00:26:50.318 --> 00:26:52.987
Or the rest of my life. so...

604
00:26:53.070 --> 00:26:54.697
What're you talking about?

605
00:26:54.780 --> 00:26:57.742
Whit and I are over.

606
00:26:59.118 --> 00:27:02.496
That's not been easy to admit. but...

607
00:27:02.580 --> 00:27:04.665
here I am.

608
00:27:04.749 --> 00:27:08.377
Ready to say it out loud. so...

609
00:27:09.253 --> 00:27:11.964
I guess I'm... happy for you?

610
00:27:12.048 --> 00:27:15.384
Thank you. It's a good thing.

611
00:27:15.468 --> 00:27:17.529
But I should say.
I'm not looking for a relationship.

612
00:27:19.263 --> 00:27:21.140
No. Charlie. I'm not. um...

613
00:27:22.516 --> 00:27:25.728
You were like a means to an end.
like. sort of a Band-Aid

614
00:27:25.811 --> 00:27:28.022
to make it all better
while the wounds healed.

615
00:27:29.315 --> 00:27:30.524
Thank you.

616
00:27:30.608 --> 00:27:33.819
I'm saying. no one goes
to Charlie Florek for a relationship.

617
00:27:33.903 --> 00:27:36.489
You're just a big. beautiful boy.

618
00:27:36.572 --> 00:27:39.992
Anyway. I guess now
is as good a time as any

619
00:27:40.076 --> 00:27:42.745
to just... end things.

620
00:27:42.828 --> 00:27:45.706
Wait a sec. Delilah.

621
00:27:45.790 --> 00:27:48.751
I do not regret a moment.

622
00:27:49.960 --> 00:27:53.464
Except for... maybe that one time
in your truck.

623
00:27:54.548 --> 00:27:56.509
I will talk to Percy about The Tavern.

624
00:28:11.982 --> 00:28:13.692
Yes?

625
00:28:13.776 --> 00:28:15.444
How do you turn down the thermostat?

626
00:28:15.528 --> 00:28:18.239
Have you first tried taking off a blanket?

627
00:28:21.450 --> 00:28:23.327
Oh.

628
00:28:23.411 --> 00:28:24.912
That's better.

629
00:28:25.704 --> 00:28:27.915
Okay. I have to work. I-I got to go.

630
00:28:27.998 --> 00:28:30.543
-Chantal?
-What is it?

631
00:28:30.626 --> 00:28:32.420
I forgot our Prime password.

632
00:28:32.503 --> 00:28:35.381
I put it in your notes app. Okay. Bye.

633
00:28:47.184 --> 00:28:50.271
-I'm not gonna interrogate you.
-What?

634
00:28:50.980 --> 00:28:53.983
Oh. Hey. I didn't see you there.

635
00:28:54.066 --> 00:28:55.151
Mm.

636
00:28:56.652 --> 00:28:58.529
Why are you working out here?

637
00:28:58.612 --> 00:29:04.410
Oh. uh. my fiancé came to visit.
and he's in our room. in bed. sick. so...

638
00:29:06.787 --> 00:29:08.080
Um...

639
00:29:08.164 --> 00:29:09.874
"Is there anything to eat?"

640
00:29:09.957 --> 00:29:12.126
I will order you Postmates.

641
00:29:12.209 --> 00:29:14.503
Yeah. we don't have Postmates
in Barry's Bay.

642
00:29:14.587 --> 00:29:18.007
That's wonderful. That's...
What do you have?

643
00:29:18.090 --> 00:29:19.967
Relax. I'll bring some soup by.

644
00:29:20.050 --> 00:29:21.135
Jordie. don't.

645
00:29:21.218 --> 00:29:22.737
-You don't have to do that.
-Oh. I am the owner

646
00:29:22.761 --> 00:29:26.056
of this establishment.
and your happiness is my priority.

647
00:29:27.933 --> 00:29:31.353
And speaking of. are you doing okay?

648
00:29:32.813 --> 00:29:35.107
I'm just a bit hungover.

649
00:29:35.191 --> 00:29:37.610
-Hungover?
-Mm-hmm.

650
00:29:37.693 --> 00:29:41.322
Well. well. well. Letting your hair down.

651
00:29:41.405 --> 00:29:45.367
No. not like that. I was just.
I was keeping Percy company.

652
00:29:46.452 --> 00:29:50.831
Right. And how's she doing anyway?
With the Sam news?

653
00:29:51.415 --> 00:29:55.211
Oh. Percy is pretty good
at her coping mechanisms.

654
00:29:58.881 --> 00:30:00.382
You know. I hate to say.

655
00:30:00.466 --> 00:30:02.801
-I'm really glad Drew got sick.
-Uh-huh.

656
00:30:07.723 --> 00:30:09.183
How'd you find this spot anyway?

657
00:30:09.266 --> 00:30:10.946
Oh. I used to come here
when I was younger.

658
00:30:12.144 --> 00:30:13.896
God.

659
00:30:13.979 --> 00:30:16.607
How many lucky guys
got to enjoy this spot with you?

660
00:30:21.779 --> 00:30:23.030
Hey. I was joking.

661
00:30:25.866 --> 00:30:27.284
Percy?

662
00:30:34.124 --> 00:30:35.626
Percy? Hey.

663
00:30:40.089 --> 00:30:43.050
I can't do this anymore.

664
00:30:43.133 --> 00:30:45.719
-Wait. what?
-It just isn't right.

665
00:30:47.054 --> 00:30:49.807
Jesus. am I finally growing up?
This sucks.

666
00:30:49.890 --> 00:30:51.267
I don't understand.

667
00:30:51.350 --> 00:30:54.436
I know. I'm-I'm sorry.

668
00:30:55.688 --> 00:30:57.523
I'll walk you back to town.

669
00:30:59.066 --> 00:31:00.626
You are being an idiot.

670
00:31:00.693 --> 00:31:04.488
Did I get the order wrong?
It's-it's my first day. so...

671
00:31:04.572 --> 00:31:07.866
-Oh. my God.
-What?

672
00:31:07.950 --> 00:31:10.703
I mean this. Being a waitress.

673
00:31:10.786 --> 00:31:12.162
I'm in Barry's Bay all summer.

674
00:31:12.246 --> 00:31:13.539
-I needed a job.
-Oh. please.

675
00:31:13.622 --> 00:31:15.102
Your plan to make Sam jealous failed.

676
00:31:15.165 --> 00:31:18.043
I know that you thought
being so close to him with your...

677
00:31:18.127 --> 00:31:22.006
bodies rubbing up against each other.
day after day. in a hot. steamy kitchen

678
00:31:22.089 --> 00:31:23.483
would make him realize
he wanted you. but...

679
00:31:23.507 --> 00:31:25.050
Okay. I did not think that.

680
00:31:27.219 --> 00:31:29.096
Okay. I...

681
00:31:29.179 --> 00:31:32.224
I know that's not gonna happen.
but maybe we can be friends.

682
00:31:32.308 --> 00:31:35.853
Does he at least know that
you broke up with Mason. again?

683
00:31:35.936 --> 00:31:37.187
Hasn't come up.

684
00:31:37.896 --> 00:31:41.817
-Make a move.
-No. he still has a girlfriend.

685
00:31:41.900 --> 00:31:43.986
Also. last summer. I made the move.
It's his turn.

686
00:31:44.069 --> 00:31:45.571
Okay. but he may not.

687
00:31:45.654 --> 00:31:49.033
Then what? You'll have wasted
your entire summer. Percy.

688
00:31:55.039 --> 00:31:57.750
I give up. You're hopeless.

689
00:31:57.833 --> 00:31:59.793
Also. you forgot my curly fries. Love you.

690
00:31:59.877 --> 00:32:02.463
♪ Nah. nah. nah ♪

691
00:32:02.546 --> 00:32:04.632
♪ Oh. no ♪

692
00:32:04.715 --> 00:32:08.636
♪ See you walking around
like it's a funeral ♪

693
00:32:08.719 --> 00:32:12.681
♪ Not so serious. girl.
why those feet cold? ♪

694
00:32:12.765 --> 00:32:14.308
♪ We just getting started ♪

695
00:32:14.391 --> 00:32:16.518
♪ don't you tiptoe. tiptoe...

696
00:32:19.063 --> 00:32:20.064
Here. I got it.

697
00:32:20.147 --> 00:32:23.025
♪ Don't waste time with a masterpiece ♪

698
00:32:23.108 --> 00:32:24.485
♪ You should be rolling with me ♪

699
00:32:24.568 --> 00:32:27.196
-♪ You should be rolling with me ♪
-♪ Ah. ah. ah ♪

700
00:32:27.279 --> 00:32:28.340
♪ You're a real-life fantasy...

701
00:32:28.364 --> 00:32:29.865
-Thanks.
-Yeah.

702
00:32:30.991 --> 00:32:34.995
♪ But you're moving so carefully.
let's start living dangerously ♪

703
00:32:35.079 --> 00:32:37.790
♪ Talk to me. baby...

704
00:32:37.873 --> 00:32:39.375
I am so sorry.

705
00:32:39.458 --> 00:32:42.503
♪ Sweet. sweet craving. whoa-oh.
let's lose our minds...

706
00:32:42.586 --> 00:32:44.254
Okay. No. I-I...

707
00:32:45.923 --> 00:32:47.233
-Truce. truce. Truce.
-Okay. All right.

708
00:32:47.257 --> 00:32:48.926
Truce. I'm gonna take this on my side.

709
00:32:49.009 --> 00:32:51.720
-Mm-hmm.
-You didn't get me so...

710
00:32:51.804 --> 00:32:52.888
Percy!

711
00:32:52.971 --> 00:32:55.516
No!

712
00:32:55.599 --> 00:32:57.643
♪ Keep on hopin' ♪

713
00:32:57.726 --> 00:32:59.206
-♪ we'll eat cake by the ocean ♪♪
-No!

714
00:32:59.269 --> 00:33:00.270
Sam?

715
00:33:02.940 --> 00:33:04.983
We're gonna be late for the movies.

716
00:33:07.027 --> 00:33:10.072
Yeah. right. Um... Sorry.
We were. uh. just doing the dishes.

717
00:33:10.155 --> 00:33:12.074
No. no. We're almost finished.
You should go.

718
00:33:14.118 --> 00:33:16.412
Yeah. Hi.

719
00:33:22.960 --> 00:33:25.546
I'm sorry. Is this weird?

720
00:33:25.629 --> 00:33:28.340
This is definitely weird.
I just. I. uh. I should've called.

721
00:33:28.424 --> 00:33:30.467
I should... I-I can't go to the motel.

722
00:33:30.551 --> 00:33:31.802
Chantal's fiancé's sick.

723
00:33:31.885 --> 00:33:33.929
and I can't go to The Tavern. obviously.

724
00:33:34.012 --> 00:33:35.889
-It's just not a place that I can...
-Inside.

725
00:33:36.932 --> 00:33:37.933
Come on.

726
00:33:41.979 --> 00:33:44.481
I thought. coming back here.
things would be...

727
00:33:44.565 --> 00:33:48.360
different. but also the same.

728
00:33:48.444 --> 00:33:50.738
And I know that makes no sense.

729
00:33:50.821 --> 00:33:52.281
No. of course it does.

730
00:33:52.364 --> 00:33:54.050
You thought all the good things
would still be here

731
00:33:54.074 --> 00:33:55.743
and all the bad stuff would be gone.

732
00:33:55.826 --> 00:33:58.537
Yeah. but all the good stuff is gone.

733
00:33:58.620 --> 00:34:04.293
and it's just the bad. and I-I-I don't
want to feel it. but I can't not.

734
00:34:04.376 --> 00:34:07.421
And I can't even do
what I normally do to distract myself.

735
00:34:07.504 --> 00:34:10.674
-What do you do?
-Hook up with hot guys.

736
00:34:10.757 --> 00:34:14.094
Well... at least that's fun.

737
00:34:14.178 --> 00:34:15.637
Except I couldn't.

738
00:34:17.556 --> 00:34:19.475
Now. I-I can't even feel...

739
00:34:21.560 --> 00:34:22.643
nothing. I...

740
00:34:23.937 --> 00:34:24.980
feel it all.

741
00:34:25.063 --> 00:34:26.732
God. I don't want this.

742
00:34:28.525 --> 00:34:29.735
Percy. what's going on?

743
00:34:31.820 --> 00:34:35.282
Hey. It's me. I'm your friend.

744
00:34:35.949 --> 00:34:36.949
I know.

745
00:34:38.452 --> 00:34:41.996
And I can't believe it.
You're... too forgiving.

746
00:34:42.623 --> 00:34:44.373
It was a long time ago.

747
00:34:45.542 --> 00:34:48.003
But you can trust me. okay?

748
00:34:57.471 --> 00:34:59.807
-Charlie?
-I just have one thing to say.

749
00:34:59.890 --> 00:35:04.228
You think that I am some
stunted. selfish man-child.

750
00:35:04.311 --> 00:35:06.647
-but I am more than that.
-Are you drunk?

751
00:35:06.730 --> 00:35:09.042
Charlie. this is... I don't think
this is the time to do this right now.

752
00:35:09.066 --> 00:35:10.418
I kept The Tavern afloat. I fucking paid

753
00:35:10.442 --> 00:35:12.945
for Sam's med school
and didn't even tell him.

754
00:35:13.028 --> 00:35:15.781
I always tip 25%.
even when the server's a dude

755
00:35:15.864 --> 00:35:17.741
because I am a good person.

756
00:35:17.825 --> 00:35:19.344
I don't care that you used me
to get over Whit.

757
00:35:19.368 --> 00:35:20.720
-Charlie...
-I mean. yeah. the sex was great.

758
00:35:20.744 --> 00:35:21.912
Oh. my God.

759
00:35:23.956 --> 00:35:24.957
Charlie?

760
00:35:25.040 --> 00:35:26.750
You were having an affair with Charlie?

761
00:35:26.834 --> 00:35:29.127
Chantal said it. and I didn't believe it.

762
00:35:30.462 --> 00:35:34.591
Persephone Fraser. I should've known.

763
00:35:34.675 --> 00:35:37.803
Man. if I could change one thing.

764
00:35:37.886 --> 00:35:39.847
do one thing different.
I would go back ten years.

765
00:35:39.930 --> 00:35:40.764
-and I would not...
-Charlie.

766
00:35:40.848 --> 00:35:42.488
I'm sorry. Can you just give us a minute?

767
00:35:42.558 --> 00:35:44.101
-Please?
-No. yeah. please.

768
00:35:44.184 --> 00:35:46.311
-Sorry.
-Take your time.

769
00:35:48.397 --> 00:35:50.667
What is wrong with you?
Do you realize what you were about to do?

770
00:35:50.691 --> 00:35:52.109
Fuck it. Who cares?

771
00:35:52.192 --> 00:35:54.570
I do. And I know you do. too.

772
00:35:54.653 --> 00:35:56.381
Oh. 'cause you and Delilah
are friends again?

773
00:35:56.405 --> 00:35:59.199
Yes. And we had an agreement.

774
00:35:59.283 --> 00:36:01.118
An agreement that
we wouldn't say anything.

775
00:36:01.201 --> 00:36:03.930
but that doesn't mean that you can come
back here and fuck up everyone's lives.

776
00:36:03.954 --> 00:36:05.455
You called me.

777
00:36:05.539 --> 00:36:08.333
And I never asked your mom
to leave me The Tavern.

778
00:36:08.417 --> 00:36:11.044
But you're choosing
to keep it. aren't you?

779
00:36:13.046 --> 00:36:15.674
Tell me this. Percy.

780
00:36:15.757 --> 00:36:19.803
you really think my mom would've given you
The Tavern if she'd known why you left?

781
00:36:20.888 --> 00:36:24.057
So. if you do decide to keep it.
it'll be under false pretenses.

782
00:36:24.141 --> 00:36:26.435
-If Sam knew...
-Charlie.

783
00:36:26.518 --> 00:36:30.939
-Sam can never ever know.
-Yeah. I know that.

784
00:36:33.233 --> 00:36:35.068
I wish I hadn't listened to my mom.

785
00:36:36.445 --> 00:36:38.864
I wish I hadn't called you.

786
00:37:07.100 --> 00:37:10.354
Do you remember
when I first asked you out?

787
00:37:10.437 --> 00:37:13.690
We were on clinical rotations.
it was the last year of med school.

788
00:37:13.774 --> 00:37:16.026
And you pretended that
you wanted to discuss a case.

789
00:37:16.109 --> 00:37:18.487
I was nervous. okay?

790
00:37:18.570 --> 00:37:21.615
But anyways. we. uh.
we kept having to postpone.

791
00:37:21.698 --> 00:37:23.992
-Mm-hmm.
-Your schedule. My schedule.

792
00:37:24.076 --> 00:37:26.828
You know. and then we finally sat down
in the hospital cafeteria

793
00:37:26.912 --> 00:37:28.580
and had that coffee at. like. 2:00 a.m.

794
00:37:28.664 --> 00:37:30.308
Yeah. and we were both too tired
to even talk.

795
00:37:30.332 --> 00:37:32.542
-Yeah. we just sat there.
-Yeah.

796
00:37:32.626 --> 00:37:33.919
It was really nice.

797
00:37:34.002 --> 00:37:35.295
It was.

798
00:37:39.007 --> 00:37:42.219
And I knew. even then.
that this is a person

799
00:37:42.302 --> 00:37:45.847
that I trust. respect.

800
00:37:47.224 --> 00:37:48.767
Who would have my back. always.

801
00:37:49.518 --> 00:37:50.978
I feel the exact same.

802
00:37:54.439 --> 00:37:56.608
This has been such a hard week for me.

803
00:37:59.736 --> 00:38:01.279
I felt scared.

804
00:38:06.326 --> 00:38:07.744
Losing my mom.

805
00:38:07.828 --> 00:38:10.872
-Yeah.
-It's been a lot.

806
00:38:12.332 --> 00:38:14.710
You know. coming home...

807
00:38:14.793 --> 00:38:19.881
I just realized so much
about who I am and what I want.

808
00:38:19.965 --> 00:38:25.053
I mean. I think being back where you
grew up must bring up a lot of feelings.

809
00:38:26.972 --> 00:38:28.390
Yeah. it really has.

810
00:38:35.022 --> 00:38:36.064
Which is why...

811
00:38:37.983 --> 00:38:41.028
there's something
we really need to talk about.

812
00:38:47.868 --> 00:38:49.327
Chantal?

813
00:38:49.411 --> 00:38:52.247
Oh. Yeah. I'm just going to the bathroom.

814
00:38:53.790 --> 00:38:55.625
What do you need?

815
00:38:55.709 --> 00:38:56.793
Nothing.

816
00:38:58.045 --> 00:38:59.212
I'm sorry.

817
00:38:59.296 --> 00:39:01.673
-It's fine.
-You're angry.

818
00:39:04.718 --> 00:39:07.512
I'm not angry. I just. I can't get sick.

819
00:39:07.596 --> 00:39:10.015
And you know that.
Y-You know what my caseload is like.

820
00:39:10.098 --> 00:39:12.142
I didn't get sick on purpose.

821
00:39:13.310 --> 00:39:16.646
Okay. so when you got in the car
with Jake this morning.

822
00:39:16.730 --> 00:39:18.774
and you weren't feeling well.

823
00:39:18.857 --> 00:39:20.692
wasn't a part of you that thought.

824
00:39:20.776 --> 00:39:22.420
"If I get sick.
Chantal will take care of me"?

825
00:39:22.444 --> 00:39:24.196
No.

826
